last_episode_to_air.name: Porsche 911 GT3 RS 4.0 & Carrera GT to the Scottish Highlands
last_episode_to_air.overview: In the first ever episode of Petrolhead Planet, Jethro Bovingdon heads to the Scottish Highlands in what might be the ultimate Porsche, a 911 GT3 RS 4.0. This motorsport-inspired 911 doesn’t disappoint, but what about the epic, desolate roads of northern Scotland that make up the North Coast 500? On this trip Jethro encounters the best and worst of British weather, but on the day the sun shines he’s joined by the iconic Carrera GT supercar, to help him determine whether the 911 GT3 RS 4.0 is the greatest Porsche of all time.

name: Petrolhead Planet
overview: Petrolhead Planet is the ultimate automotive travel show. Not only is Jethro Bovingdon your guide to the greatest roads in the world, but he tells you how to find them, too! And if that’s not enough, in every episode Jethro has a “modern classic” along for the adventure. We’re not talking any old car, either, but the crème de la crème of iconic performance cars from the ’80s, ’90s, and ’00s—think Porsche 911 GT3 RS 4.0, McLaren P1, that sort of thing.
